    "body": "Great idea, and something I think we should definitely implement.\n\nI think the complications of Lighthouse's previous config file implementation stemmed from mutating the file to try to keep it in sync with the CLI params. I think the behaviour you describe makes a lot more sense: the file should be read-only from Lighthouse's perspective, has to be explicitly provided on the CLI (no surprising default location), consists _only_ of CLI flags, and is overridden by flags provided explicitly (no consistency checks between file and CLI).\n\nAs a format I think TOML would probably be best",
