    "body": "Rather than create a new issue, bumping this one to add another voice requesting config parameter support. Currently integrating lighthouse support into Node Launcher backend for Node Pilot (https://github.com/decentralized-authority/node-launcher/issues/68). Users will be limited in extending or customizing a lighthouse instance running within Node Pilot when the commands are fed in at runtime, so we prefer to run clients with flags read in via a config toml or yml file. \r\n\r\nI code to support this feature has been merged into the unstable branch months ago. Is there a  plan to include this soon in an upcoming release?",
